headline: D-Wave Stock Surges 20% on Advantage2 Release. ‘It’s Energy-Efficient Computing for Hard Problems.’
summary: D-Wave Quantum  said Tuesday that its sixth-generation quantum system had become available over the cloud, marking another development in the race to develop commercially viable quantum computers.  For now, customers will be able to access Advantage2 through D-Wave’s Leap cloud service, though physical machines will be deployed gradually over the next few years.  Management cited the technology’s applications in tasks such as supply-chain optimization and resource allocation, outside the realm of what classical machines could effectively handle.
